1 olive oil
1 tomato
1 packet beef mince
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
2 Butter Burger Buns
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet creamy pesto dressing
1 Kumara
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
2 clove garlic
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Peel and cut kumara into fries and place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle generously with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then add a dash of water to the tray and roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
• In last 5 minutes of cook time, sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese over fries and bake until melted.

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic. Thinly slice tomato.
• In a large bowl, combine garlic, beef mince, fine breadcrumbs, Aussie spice blend and egg, then season with salt and pepper.
• Shape beef mixture into evenly sized patties, slightly larger than the burger buns. You should get 1 patty per person. Transfer to a plate.

• When fries have 15 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook beef patties until just cooked through, 4-5 minutes each side.
• Meanwhile, bake butter burger buns directly on a wire oven rack until heated through, 3 minutes.

TIP: If your patties begin to char, reduce the heat to medium.

• In a medium bowl, combine a drizzle of olive oil and balsamic vinegar. Add mixed salad leaves, season to taste and toss to coat.
• Slice burger buns in half and spread the bases with creamy pesto dressing.
• Top with a beef patty, some tomato and dressed salad leaves.
• Serve with Parmesan kumara fries.